{
  "texts": [
    "Anchors or scoped rules (Ribeiro et al. 2018) are high-precision easy-to-understand ifthen rules.",
    "They portray feature conditions together with a predictive outcome.",
    "The rules are called Anchors because any changes to other features than the ones mentioned, will not result in another prediction.",
    "In contrast to e.g., LIME, Anchors will provide a region of instances to describe the model's behavior.",
    "They are consequently less instance-specific."
  ]
}